				<category name="Features">
					<category name="No Broken Chests Near Denial Subroutine">
						<comment># No Broken Chests Near Denial Subroutine v1.0.0</comment>
						<comment># by Apocalyptech</comment>
						<comment># Licensed under Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal</comment>
						<comment>#</comment>
						<comment># The Denial Subroutine arena (in Cluster 99002 0V3RL00K) has six bandit "coolers" which don't actually</comment>
						<comment># work -- they open and spawn their items, but the items can't actually be picked up.  This mod changes</comment>
						<comment># them to be the round ammo chests instead, so at least they work.</comment>
						<hotfix name="Name" level="Ma_RightCluster_P">
							<code profiles="default">set Ma_RightCluster_Combat.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.WillowPopulationOpportunityPoint_44 PopulationDef PopulationDefinition'GD_Ma_Population_Treasure.Lootables.BanditAmmo_Marigold'</code>
							<code profiles="default">set Ma_RightCluster_Combat.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.WillowPopulationOpportunityPoint_131 PopulationDef PopulationDefinition'GD_Ma_Population_Treasure.Lootables.BanditAmmo_Marigold'</code>

				<category name="Skinpool Reassignments (DO NOT UNCHECK)" locked="true">
					<comment># TPS Skinpool Reassignments v1.1.0</comment>
					<comment># by Apocalyptech (based on the BL2 UCP section with the same purpose)</comment>
					<comment># Licensed under Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal</comment>
					<comment>#</comment>
					<comment># Frees up 624 skin/head pools for use by TPS mods.  This</comment>
					<comment># is possible because the default skin/head pools use an effectively</comment>
					<comment># unnecessary intermediate pool inbetween the pool that's actually</comment>
					<comment># used for drops and the skins/heads themselves.  The BL2 UCP does</comment>
					<comment># this and uses the resulting pools for custom boss drops, and</comment>
					<comment># other mods do so as well.</comment>
					<comment>#</comment>
					<comment># See https://github.com/BLCM/BLCMods/wiki/TPS-Custom-Skin-and-Head-Pool-Registry</comment>
					<category name="Skinpool Hotfixes">
						<hotfix name="ApocHotfix" level="None">

				<category name="Spawn Only COMs of your character">
					<comment># TPS No Wasted COMs v1.1.0</comment>
					<comment># by Apocalyptech</comment>
					<comment># Licensed under Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal</comment>
					<comment>#</comment>
					<comment># Sets the game to only drop COMs for the player classes who are actually</comment>
					<comment># in the game at the time.  Once a player class has joined the game, the</comment>
					<comment># only way to remove that character's COMs from the drop pools is to exit</comment>
					<comment># to the main menu and re-execute the patch.</comment>
					<category name="Initial Clear">
						<comment># Do an initial set to clear out the COM item pools.  This is actually</comment>
						<comment># only required if you're looking to "clear out" a pool after a character's</comment>
						<comment># left the game, and must be done by exiting out to the main menu and re-</comment>
						<comment># executing the mod/patch.</comment>

			<category name="mods">
				<category name="BuggyReplace">
					<comment>#Credit: Darkhell 99% lax 1%</comment>
					<comment>#Makes the Stingray have priority over the Moonbuggy in the spawn station, and changes the laser buggy into the Stingray. The missle buggy will remain as a buggy to prevent some softlocks and stuff.</comment>
					<category name="stingray1">
						<hotfix name="buggyreplace" level="None">
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Globals.VehicleSpawnStation.VSSUI_LaserBuggy PathToVSSDefinition GD_Co_StingRay_Streaming.VSS.VSS_StingRay_FlakBurst</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Globals.VehicleSpawnStation.VSSUI_LaserBuggy VehicleName Flak Cannon Stingray</code>
							<code profiles="default">set VSSUIDefinition GD_Globals.VehicleSpawnStation.VSSUI_LaserBuggy VehicleFamilyDefinition 'GD_Globals.VehicleSpawnStation.VehicleFamily_StingRay'</code>
						</hotfix>
					</category>
				</category>

									<code profiles="default">set GD_Ma_AmmoMachine.IO_Ma_AmmoMachine:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0 BehaviorSequences[1].ConsolidatedOutputLinkData[6].ActivateDelay 0.8</code>
								</hotfix>
							</category>
						</category>

				<category name="TPS - Uncapped Pause / Main Menu Settings (imported from TPSUncappedPauseMenuSettings.blcm)">
					<comment>Mod written by GitHub: Our Lord And Savior Gabe Newell / Nexus Mods: OB4MA</comment>
					<comment></comment>
					<comment>This mod simply allows more customization in terms of scrollable settings accessed via the pause or main menu.</comment>
					<comment>These settings, unlike other methods, WILL KEEP THE VALUE even if you do not execute the mod again.</comment>
					<comment>However, if you mess with them again they will go back to normal value ranges.</comment>
					<comment></comment>
					<comment>There is nothing to customize in this file, you do all of the customizing in-game.</comment>
					<comment>You can edit the ranges for values if you would like to.</comment>
					<comment></comment>
					<comment>-----------------------------------------</comment>
					<category name="Player FOV">

					<comment>-----------------------------------------</comment>
					<comment>CINEMATIC MODE</comment>
					<comment>-----------------------------------------</comment>
					<comment>This mode can be used to remove the first person HUD, enemy health bars and interactive object icons (press E to pickup) while retaining full functionality of everything.</comment>
					<comment>Press Esc or Pause, go to options, then video, then set the HUD scale to 0.</comment>

					<comment>Allows you re-enable the previously one-way only fast travel stations, lets you move them to any</comment>
					<comment> map without one, and adds a few QoL changes to go along with these new stations</comment>

					<comment> through the story</comment>

							<hotfix name="EnableLaserBossTravel" level="Laser_P">
								<code profiles="default">set SeqAct_ToggleHidden'Laser_P.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.Main_Sequence.SeqAct_ToggleHidden_1' OutputLinks ()</code>
								<code profiles="default">set SeqAct_ToggleHidden'Laser_P.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.Main_Sequence.SeqAct_ToggleHidden_1' VariableLinks ()</code>
								<code profiles="default">set SeqAct_Toggle'Laser_P.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.Main_Sequence.SeqAct_Toggle_4' OutputLinks ()</code>
								<code profiles="default">set SeqAct_Toggle'Laser_P.TheWorld:PersistentLevel.Main_Sequence.SeqAct_Toggle_4' VariableLinks ()</code>

				<category name="TPS Rarity Color Fix">
					<comment>#NoMoreJebaited</comment>
					<comment>By Koby</comment>
					<comment>Changes the rarity color of unique aftermarket items to a dark teal to be more distinguishable from other items.</comment>
					<comment>Changes the color of DLC legendaries to a dark orange.</comment>
					<comment>Changes the color of Moxxi weapons to a blood red.</comment>
					<comment>Makes "Glitch Rarity" weapons be below uniques and above purples.</comment>
					<comment>Changes the order of items in the inventory: DLC Legendary -> Legendary -> Moxxi -> Unique -> Glitch -> Very Rare...</comment>
					<comment>Has an optional module to turn all Heads and Skins to a grey-ish color.</comment>
					<comment>Full BLCMM support!</comment>
					<comment>Thanks to FromDarkHell for writing me a script for the Heads and Skins.</comment>
					<comment>INCOMPATIBILITY NOTE:</comment>
					<comment>This mod will most likely conflict with any mod which changes rarity colors and rarities of items.</comment>
					<comment>If you have basic modding and reading knowledge, you can fix the rarity in the weapon/item mod yourself.</comment>
					<category name="Rarity Color Change" MUT="true">
						<category name="Normal">
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Globals.General.Globals RarityLevelColors 				</category>
				<category name="TPS Better Loot Mod">
					<comment># TPS Better Loot Mod v1.1.0</comment>
					<comment># by Apocalyptech</comment>
					<comment># Licensed under Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal</comment>
					<comment>#</comment>
					<comment># All sorts of tweaks to loot in general, with the aim of basically making all</comment>
					<comment># the loot drops in the game "better".  In the default configuration, there is</comment>
					<comment># a very increased chance of blues/purples/glitch/legendary items across the</comment>
					<comment># board, slightly more Moonstone, and far better badass and boss drops.  Also</comment>
					<comment># basically all game items will be available as regular world drops, including</comment>
					<comment># uniques.  Glitch weapons are available outside the Claptastic Voyage DLC,</comment>
					<comment># though they're more common when in the DLC levels.</comment>
					<comment>#</comment>
					<comment># The specifics of much of the mod, however, including drop quality, can be</comment>
					<comment># configured below.  Every section apart from "Base Mod Configuration" is</comment>
					<comment># intended to be user-configurable.</comment>
					<category name="Base Mod Configuration">
						<comment># This category is mostly considered stuff you'll be unlikely to toggle on/off</comment>
						<comment># individually.  The categories which are intended to be user-settable are all below</comment>
						<comment># this one, starting with "Legendary Pool Improvements" and ending with</comment>
						<comment># the Common Pistol Chest Configuration section.</comment>
						<comment>#</comment>
						<comment># It's not really a "base" config -- at lot of the "meat" of the mod is in the</comment>
						<comment># user-selectable areas, but I was at a loss for a better name for it.</comment>
						<category name="Base Early Game Unlocks" locked="true">
							<comment># To prevent the possibility of enemies spawning in the early game without any</comment>
							<comment># weapons, we're forcing a number of unlocks to happen right away.  In terms of</comment>
							<comment># unlocks, we'll always assume that the game's effectively running at level 8.</comment>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_02:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_03:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_04:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_05:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_06:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_07:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_08:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
						</category>
						<category name="Loot Pool Tweaks">
							<category name="Normalize Gun Type Drops">
								<comment># In the vanilla game, pistols are the most likely drop, followed by</comment>
								<comment># ARs/SMGs/Shotguns, then snipers/lasers, and then launchers.  This</comment>
								<comment># normalizes the probabilities for Pistols/ARs/SMGs/Shotguns, and</comment>
								<comment># makes snipers, lasers, and launchers more likely (though still not</comment>
								<comment># as likely as the others)</comment>
								<hotfix name="ApocHotfix" level="None">
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_01_Common BalancedItems[0].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_02_Uncommon BalancedItems[0].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_04_Rare BalancedItems[0].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_05_VeryRare BalancedItems[0].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_06_Legendary BalancedItems[0].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_01_Common BalancedItems[1].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_02_Uncommon BalancedItems[1].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_04_Rare BalancedItems[1].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_05_VeryRare BalancedItems[1].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_06_Legendary BalancedItems[1].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_01_Common BalancedItems[2].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_02_Uncommon BalancedItems[2].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_04_Rare BalancedItems[2].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_05_VeryRare BalancedItems[2].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_06_Legendary BalancedItems[2].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_01_Common BalancedItems[3].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>

									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_04_Rare BalancedItems[3].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_05_VeryRare BalancedItems[3].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_06_Legendary BalancedItems[3].Probability.BaseValueConstant 100</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_01_Common BalancedItems[4].Probability.BaseValueConstant 80</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_All_02_Uncommon BalancedItems[4].Probability.BaseValueConstant 80</code>

					<category name="Remove Level-Based Loot Restrictions (superset of UCP 2.1)">
						<comment># This should allow all loot to spawn at the very beginning of the game, including</comment>
						<comment># all types of weapons, part types, elements, etc.  This is a superset of similar</comment>
						<comment># functionality already present in UCP 2.1, though this does more than what UCP</comment>
						<comment># does.  There is no conflict with having both enabled at the same time, though</comment>
						<comment># UCP goes about it in a different way than we do here.</comment>
						<comment>#</comment>
						<comment># Copied from TPS Early Bloomer v1.1.0 by Apocalyptech, though with a few of the</comment>
						<comment># unlocks moved into the main mod section.</comment>
						<comment>#</comment>
						<comment># This section is already also included in TPS Cold Dead Hands, but there's no problem</comment>
						<comment># with having it enabled in both.</comment>
						<category name="Main Unlocks">
							<comment># Note that we omit Gamestage_24 on purpose here, because that is used to</comment>
							<comment># determine Weapon Slot SDU rewards during playthrough 1 in the main storyline.</comment>
							<comment># Nothing else in the game uses 24, so we're leaving it.</comment>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_09:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_10:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_11:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_12:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_13:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_14:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_15:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_16:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_17:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_18:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.Scheduling.Gamestage_19:ConstantAttributeValueResolver_0 ConstantValue 1</code>

						<category name="Remove Unique \"Shift\" Weapons from Global Rare Pools">
							<comment># TPS includes four Unique weapons in with the global world blue/rare</comment>
							<comment># drops, since they don't otherwise have specific drops.  This happens</comment>
							<comment># for the Boomacorn, Ol'Painful, Jack-O-Cannon, and The Machine.  Since</comment>
							<comment># we're adding these to our Legendary pool, and we're increasing blue/rare</comment>

							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># NOTE: There will be two weapons columns in some categories - "Main" refers to drops when</comment>
							<comment># in the main game levels, and "Clap" refers to drops when in Claptastic Voyage levels.</comment>

						<category name="Very Good Quality">
							<comment># Inbetween the former "Lootsplosion" and "Reasonable" presets.</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># NOTE: There will be two weapons columns in some categories - "Main" refers to drops when</comment>
							<comment># in the main game levels, and "Clap" refers to drops when in Claptastic Voyage levels.</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># World Drop Rates (regular enemies):</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment>#                        Main     Clap</comment>
							<comment>#                     Weapons  Weapons  Items</comment>
							<comment>#     Common (white):     17%      16%    18%</comment>
							<comment>#   Uncommon (green):     40%      38%    41%</comment>
							<comment>#        Rare (blue):     28%      27%    29%</comment>
							<comment># Very Rare (purple):     11%      11%    12%</comment>
							<comment>#      Glitch (pink):      3%       7%    --</comment>
							<comment># Legendary (orange):   0.56%    0.55%  0.58%</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># Additional gear likely to be dropped by Badass enemies:</comment>
							<comment># (NOTE: "Super" and "Ultimate" actually refer to specific boss-type enemies in</comment>
							<comment># the game, not the more generic badasses you more commonly encounter.)</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment>#                       Main    Clap |   All |     Main      Clap</comment>
							<comment>#                     Badass  Badass | Super | Ultimate  Ultimate</comment>
							<comment>#        Rare (blue):     --      -- |     1 |       --        --</comment>
							<comment># Very Rare (purple):    0.3    0.15 |   0.8 |      1.2      0.80</comment>
							<comment>#      Glitch (pink):   0.22    0.33 |   0.6 |        1       1.4</comment>
							<comment># Legendary (orange):     --      -- |   0.1 |        1         1</comment>
							<comment>#  "Epic" chest drop:    0.1     0.1 |     1 |      1.5       1.5</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># Treasure Chests:</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment>#                     Regular Chests  |   "Epic" Chests  |  Glitched "Epic" Chests</comment>
							<comment>#                     Weapons  Items  |  Weapons  Items  |  Weapons</comment>
							<comment>#     Common (white):     20%    22%  |       0%     0%  |       0%</comment>
							<comment>#   Uncommon (green):     40%    43%  |      15%    18%  |      12%</comment>
							<comment>#        Rare (blue):     25%    27%  |      45%    53%  |      37%</comment>
							<comment># Very Rare (purple):      7%     8%  |      23%    27%  |      19%</comment>
							<comment>#      Glitch (pink):      7%    --   |      15%    --   |      29%</comment>
							<comment># Legendary (orange):      1%     1%  |       2%     2%  |       3%</comment>
							<category name="Better Enemy Drops">
								<comment># Note that the majority of the drop tweaks happen in the main section of</comment>
								<comment># the mod.</comment>
								<category name="Badass Enemies">
									<comment># Badass drops are actually already pretty good in TPS, but we're tweaking</comment>

							<comment># Original "Reasonable" presets.  Attempts to be somewhat restrained.</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># NOTE: There will be two weapons columns in some categories - "Main" refers to drops when</comment>
							<comment># in the main game levels, and "Clap" refers to drops when in Claptastic Voyage levels.</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># World Drop Rates (regular enemies):</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment>#                        Main     Clap</comment>
							<comment>#                     Weapons  Weapons  Items</comment>
							<comment>#     Common (white):     33%      32%    33%</comment>
							<comment>#   Uncommon (green):     35%      35%    36%</comment>
							<comment>#        Rare (blue):     25%      25%    26%</comment>
							<comment># Very Rare (purple):      5%       4%     5%</comment>
							<comment>#      Glitch (pink):      2%       4%    --</comment>
							<comment># Legendary (orange):   0.25%    0.25%  0.26%</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># Additional gear likely to be dropped by Badass enemies:</comment>
							<comment># (NOTE: "Super" and "Ultimate" actually refer to specific boss-type enemies in</comment>
							<comment># the game, not the more generic badasses you more commonly encounter.)</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment>#                       Main    Clap |   All |     Main      Clap</comment>
							<comment>#                     Badass  Badass | Super | Ultimate  Ultimate</comment>
							<comment>#        Rare (blue):     --      -- |     1 |       --        --</comment>
							<comment># Very Rare (purple):    0.2     0.1 |   0.4 |        1       0.4</comment>
							<comment>#      Glitch (pink):   0.15    0.25 |  0.15 |      0.4         1</comment>
							<comment># Legendary (orange):     --      -- |  0.03 |     0.08      0.08</comment>
							<comment>#  "Epic" chest drop:    0.1     0.1 |     1 |        3         3</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>

							<comment>#</comment>

						<category name="Improved Quality">
							<comment># For anyone who thought that "Reasonable" was still OP but doesn't want to go all the way to Stock</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># NOTE: There will be two weapons columns in some categories - "Main" refers to drops when</comment>
							<comment># in the main game levels, and "Clap" refers to drops when in Claptastic Voyage levels.</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># World Drop Rates (regular enemies):</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment>#                        Main     Clap</comment>
							<comment>#                     Weapons  Weapons  Items</comment>
							<comment>#     Common (white):     46%      46%    47%</comment>
							<comment>#   Uncommon (green):     46%      46%    47%</comment>
							<comment>#        Rare (blue):      6%       6%     6%</comment>
							<comment># Very Rare (purple):   0.58%    0.57%  0.58%</comment>
							<comment>#      Glitch (pink):   0.58%       2%    --</comment>
							<comment># Legendary (orange):   0.12%    0.11%  0.12%</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># Additional gear likely to be dropped by Badass enemies:</comment>
							<comment># (NOTE: "Super" and "Ultimate" actually refer to specific boss-type enemies in</comment>
							<comment># the game, not the more generic badasses you more commonly encounter.)</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment>#                       Main    Clap |   All |     Main      Clap</comment>
							<comment>#                     Badass  Badass | Super | Ultimate  Ultimate</comment>
							<comment>#        Rare (blue):     --      -- |     1 |       --        --</comment>
							<comment># Very Rare (purple):    0.2     0.2 |   0.2 |      0.8       0.8</comment>
							<comment>#      Glitch (pink):    0.1     0.3 |  0.15 |      0.4       1.1</comment>
							<comment># Legendary (orange):     --      -- |  0.03 |     0.07      0.07</comment>
							<comment>#  "Epic" chest drop:   0.05    0.05 |   0.8 |      1.5       1.5</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># Treasure Chests:</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment>#                     Regular Chests  |   "Epic" Chests  |  Glitched "Epic" Chests</comment>
							<comment>#                     Weapons  Items  |  Weapons  Items  |  Weapons</comment>
							<comment>#     Common (white):     40%    41%  |       0%     0%  |       0%</comment>
							<comment>#   Uncommon (green):     45%    46%  |      38%    40%  |      35%</comment>
							<comment>#        Rare (blue):     10%    10%  |      47%    49%  |      43%</comment>
							<comment># Very Rare (purple):      2%     2%  |      10%    11%  |      10%</comment>
							<comment>#      Glitch (pink):      2%    --   |       4%    --   |      11%</comment>
							<comment># Legendary (orange):   0.15%  0.15%  |    0.62%  0.65%  |       1%</comment>

						<category name="Stock-ish Quality">
							<comment># This is not *actually* stock values, but it's somewhat close.  Not recommended, but You Do You(tm).</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># NOTE: There will be two weapons columns in some categories - "Main" refers to drops when</comment>
							<comment># in the main game levels, and "Clap" refers to drops when in Claptastic Voyage levels.</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># World Drop Rates (regular enemies):</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment>#                        Main     Clap</comment>
							<comment>#                     Weapons  Weapons  Items</comment>
							<comment>#     Common (white):     87%      87%    87%</comment>
							<comment>#   Uncommon (green):     12%      12%    12%</comment>
							<comment>#        Rare (blue):      1%       1%     1%</comment>
							<comment># Very Rare (purple):   0.12%    0.12%  0.12%</comment>
							<comment>#      Glitch (pink):   0.12%    0.58%    --</comment>
							<comment># Legendary (orange):   0.03%    0.03%  0.03%</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># Additional gear likely to be dropped by Badass enemies:</comment>
							<comment># (NOTE: "Super" and "Ultimate" actually refer to specific boss-type enemies in</comment>
							<comment># the game, not the more generic badasses you more commonly encounter.)</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment>#                       Main    Clap |   All |     Main      Clap</comment>
							<comment>#                     Badass  Badass | Super | Ultimate  Ultimate</comment>
							<comment>#        Rare (blue):     --      -- |   0.5 |       --        --</comment>
							<comment># Very Rare (purple):    0.1     0.1 |   0.1 |      0.5       0.5</comment>
							<comment>#      Glitch (pink):   0.05     0.1 |   0.1 |      0.4         1</comment>
							<comment># Legendary (orange):     --      -- |  0.03 |     0.06      0.06</comment>
							<comment>#  "Epic" chest drop:      0       0 |   0.5 |     0.55      0.55</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment># Treasure Chests:</comment>
							<comment>#</comment>
							<comment>#                     Regular Chests  |   "Epic" Chests  |  Glitched "Epic" Chests</comment>
							<comment>#                     Weapons  Items  |  Weapons  Items  |  Weapons</comment>
							<comment>#     Common (white):     41%    42%  |       0%     0%  |       0%</comment>
							<comment>#   Uncommon (green):     55%    55%  |      87%    89%  |      81%</comment>
							<comment>#        Rare (blue):      3%     3%  |       9%     9%  |       8%</comment>
							<comment># Very Rare (purple):   0.41%  0.42%  |       2%     2%  |       2%</comment>
							<comment>#      Glitch (pink):   0.41%    --   |       2%    --   |       8%</comment>
							<comment># Legendary (orange):      0%     0%  |    0.26%  0.27%  |    0.49%</comment>
							<category name="Better Enemy Drops">
								<comment># Note that the majority of the drop tweaks happen in the main section of</comment>
								<comment># the mod.</comment>
								<category name="Badass Enemies">
									<comment># Badass drops are actually already pretty good in TPS, but we're tweaking</comment>

							<category name="Holodome Onslaught Unique Drop Rates">
								<comment># Pretty much all the "custom" Holodome Onslaught enemies will drop from a</comment>
								<comment># custom pool containing all the items added in that DLC.  By default it's</comment>
								<comment># 6.6%.  We're buffing that a bit.  You won't see many of these during the</comment>
								<comment># first few rounds of the Onslaught, but in the final stages, stuff will</comment>
								<comment># be dropping quite frequently.</comment>

					<category name="Provide Common Pistol Chests for \"To Arms!\" mission (choose one)" MUT="true">
						<category name="Don't Provide Common Pistol Chest (improve OzKit-Only Chests, though)">
							<comment># In Triton Flats, near where Dierdre is found, there are two chests which</comment>
							<comment># will always contain only OzKits (there's also an ECHO from a disappointed</comment>
							<comment># OzKit graphic designer in there).  This section will bump up the rarity of</comment>
							<comment># those OzKits to be greens and blues.</comment>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Itempools.ListDefs.AmmoCrateLoot_OzKitsOnly LootData ((ConfigurationName="AmmoCrate",bIgnoreGameStageRestrictions=False,LootGameStageVarianceFormula=None,Weight=(BaseValueConstant=100.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000),ItemAttachments=((ItemPool=ItemPoolDefinition'GD_Itempools.MoonItemPools.Pool_MoonItem_02_Uncommon',PoolProbability=(BaseValueConstant=1.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000),InvBalanceDefinition=None,AttachmentPointName="Ammo1"),(ItemPool=ItemPoolDefinition'GD_Itempools.MoonItemPools.Pool_MoonItem_04_Rare',PoolProbability=(BaseValueConstant=1.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000),InvBalanceDefinition=None,AttachmentPointName="Ammo2"),(ItemPool=ItemPoolDefinition'GD_Itempools.MoonItemPools.Pool_MoonItem_02_Uncommon',PoolProbability=(BaseValueConstant=1.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000),InvBalanceDefinition=None,AttachmentPointName="Ammo3"))))</code>
						</category>
						<category name="Provide Common Pistol Chests (removes OzKit-only chests)">
							<comment># The mission "To Arms!" was already rather annoying to begin with, but with this</comment>
							<comment># mod enabled, it's actually one of the harder ones to complete, especially if</comment>
							<comment># you're also using some vendor improvements.  Enabling this folder will cause a</comment>
							<comment># few chests to appear in the same room as the dead drop, which always contain</comment>
							<comment># common pistols.  It uses the previously-OzKit-only chests found near Deirdre</comment>
							<comment># to do this, so those chests will no longer be ozkit chests if you have this</comment>
							<comment># enabled.</comment>
							<code profiles="">set GD_Itempools.ListDefs.AmmoCrateLoot_OzKitsOnly LootData ((ConfigurationName="AmmoCrate",bIgnoreGameStageRestrictions=False,LootGameStageVarianceFormula=None,Weight=(BaseValueConstant=100.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000),ItemAttachments=((ItemPool=ItemPoolDefinition'GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_Pistols_01_Common',PoolProbability=(BaseValueConstant=1.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000),InvBalanceDefinition=None,AttachmentPointName="Ammo1"),(ItemPool=ItemPoolDefinition'GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_Pistols_01_Common',PoolProbability=(BaseValueConstant=1.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000),InvBalanceDefinition=None,AttachmentPointName="Ammo2"),(ItemPool=ItemPoolDefinition'GD_Itempools.WeaponPools.Pool_Weapons_Pistols_01_Common',PoolProbability=(BaseValueConstant=1.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000),InvBalanceDefinition=None,AttachmentPointName="Ammo3"))))</code>
							<hotfix name="ApocHotfix" level="Moon_P">

				<category name="TPS Configurable Slot Machines">
					<comment># TPS Configurable Slot Machines v1.0.0</comment>
					<comment># by Apocalyptech</comment>
					<comment># Licensed under Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal</comment>
					<comment>#</comment>
					<comment># Allows you to configure the base game's slot machines, of the sort in Concordia.</comment>
					<comment># The default configuration is identical to the stock slot machines - you must choose</comment>
					<comment># some options to actually have any changes take effect.</comment>
					<comment>#</comment>
					<comment># Keep in mind that increasing the frequency of one kind of item can end up impacting</comment>
					<comment># the frequencies of other items.  Categories with "Quality" in the title should keep</comment>
					<comment># the frequencies the same.</comment>
					<comment>#</comment>
					<comment># Also note that if you're in developer mode in BLCMM v1.1.6, most of this mod will</comment>
					<comment># complain that things will be overwritten by the game -- that's actually an error on</comment>
					<comment># BLCMM's part, and should hopefully be fixed by v1.1.7.</comment>
					<category name="Mod Setup" locked="true">
						<comment># These are some statements which are required for some of the later statements</comment>
						<comment># to work properly.</comment>
						<hotfix name="ApocHotfix" level="None">
							<code profiles="default">set GD_SlotMachine.SlotMachine:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0 BehaviorSequences[1].BehaviorData2[4].LinkedVariables.ArrayIndexAndLength 0</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_SlotMachine.SlotMachine:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0 BehaviorSequences[1].BehaviorData2[42].LinkedVariables.ArrayIndexAndLength 0</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_SlotMachine.SlotMachine:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0 BehaviorSequences[1].BehaviorData2[97].LinkedVariables.ArrayIndexAndLength 0</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_SlotMachine.SlotMachine:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0 BehaviorSequences[1].BehaviorData2[102].LinkedVariables.ArrayIndexAndLength 0</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_SlotMachine.SlotMachine:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0 BehaviorSequences[1].BehaviorData2[126].LinkedVariables.ArrayIndexAndLength 0</code>
						</hotfix>
					</category>
					<category name="Weapons">

				<category name="TPS - Respawning Loot">
					<comment>Mod written by GitHub: (Our Lord And Savior Gabe Newell) / Nexus Mods: (OB4MA)</comment>
					<comment></comment>
					<comment>This mod makes all objects refresh themselves upon leaving and re-entering the map.</comment>
					<comment>This allows you to keep getting stuff without save and quitting.</comment>
					<comment>This refreshes vendors too.  So now the timer for the item of the day is only if you stay in that map for however long.</comment>
					<comment>As far as I am aware it does NOT affect enemies at all.</comment>
					<comment></comment>
					<category name="Super Complicated Stuff - Leave Enabled" locked="true">
						<category name="Code">
							<code profiles="default">set GearboxFramework.Default__PopulationDefinition bTotalResetOnLevelLoad True</code>
						</category>
					</category>
				</category>
				<category name="TPSRespawningEnemiesAndAllies">
					<comment>Mod written by GitHub: (Our Lord And Savior Gabe Newell) / Nexus Mods: (OB4MA)</comment>
					<comment></comment>
					<comment>This mod makes all enemy and ally spawns refresh upon map exit and re-entering.</comment>
					<comment>This allows you to keep getting stuff without save and quitting.</comment>
					<comment>For example, you can farm the Bunker, Doc Mercy, Boll and whoever else who doesn't normally respawn without save and quitting.</comment>
					<comment>This can be useful for things like Anarchy stacks.</comment>
					<comment></comment>
					<category name="Super Complicated Stuff - Leave Enabled" locked="true">
						<category name="Code">
							<code profiles="default">set WillowGame.Default__WillowPopulationDefinition bTotalResetOnLevelLoad True</code>
						</category>
					</category>
					<comment></comment>
					<comment>OPTIONAL: Customize this part to your liking, the default value here is the normal respawn delay.</comment>
					<comment></comment>
					<category name="OPTIONAL: Change Respawn Delay For AI.">
						<code profiles="">set GD_Globals.General.Globals RespawnDelayInSeconds 1500.000000</code>
					</category>
				</category>
